    <text id="B0029T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell's letter details the supplies he is sending to Jackson, asking him to
                    use them with all possible economy.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau of Refugees, Freedmen, and Abandoned Lands<lb/>Head Quarters 9th District
                    Department of the Potomac
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. <abbr expan="Thomas">Tho<hi rend="super"
                        >s</hi></abbr> P. Jackson<lb/>Agent<lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia"
                        >Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-08-17"><abbr expan="August">Aug</abbr> 17<hi rend="super">th</hi>, 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, Va.</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I have this day forwarded to your address the following articles of Stationery,
                        <unclear>inq</unclear> 12 <unclear>Qs</unclear> Letter Paper, 3
                    <unclear>Qs</unclear> Cap. <unclear>di</unclear>, 200 Envelopes <abbr
                        expan="official">off<hi rend="super">l</hi></abbr> 50 00 Letter, 4
                        <unclear>Bb-Juk-Blk</unclear> 1 <unclear>Bob.</unclear> Red Ink 1 Bb.
                        <unclear>Mucilage</unclear> 75 <unclear>glut Rurs</unclear> 8 Penholders, 2
                    Sheets Blotting Board, 6 Sheets Envelope Paper, we have no Lead Pencils.</p>

                <p>This supply is greatly in Excess of the Bureau Allowance, and must be used with
                    all economy consistent with the proper transaction of business- </p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/><abbr expan="Your Obedient Servant">Your Ob
                        Srvt</abbr></salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt.</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S.a.C.</abbr></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Please acknowledge receipt</seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
